[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_ActivateSpire X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Activate Spire"
LocLongDescription="Activate one of your spires. It can use abilities this turn."
LocHelpText="Activate one of your spires. It can use abilities this turn."
LocFlyOverText="Activate Spire"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"\"\n\nSpires always provide cover, and their passive abilities always apply to nearby squadmates. However, to use any of the spire's active abilities, the Architect has to activate it.\n\n<Bullet/> - Free action\n<Bullet/> - Usable once per turn\n<Bullet /> Requires line-of-sight to the spire"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_Decommission X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Decommission"
LocLongDescription="Destroy this spire."
LocHelpText="Destroy this spire."
LocFlyOverText="Decommission"
LocPromotionPopupText="Would it make you feel better if it were called \"Retire\"?"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_SpawnSpire X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Build Spire"
LocLongDescription="Build a spire. Spires provide high cover."
LocHelpText="Build a spire. Spires provide high cover."
LocFlyOverText="Build Spire"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"What you leave behind is not what is engraved in stone monuments, but what is woven into the lives of others.\"\n- Pericles\n\nSpires are the focal point of most Architect abilities. They provide cover, and confer additional benefits as the architect is promoted.\n\n<Bullet/> Costs one action\n<Bullet/> Doesn't end your turn\n<Bullet/> <Ability:SpawnSpireRange/>-tile range\n<Bullet/> <Ability:SpawnSpireCooldown/>-turn cooldown"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_Shelter X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Shelter Array"
LocLongDescription="Your spires gain Shelter, which grants allies who end their turn adjacent to the spire a small shield. Shelter doesn't stack."
LocHelpText="Your spires gain Shelter, which grants allies who end their turn adjacent to the spire a small shield. Shelter doesn't stack."
LocFlyOverText="Shelter"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"I don't think that architecture is only about shelter, is only about a very simple enclosure. It should be able to excite you, to calm you, to make you think.\"\n- Zaha Hadid\n\n<Bullet/> Passive\n<Bullet/> Shield lasts <Ability:ShelterShieldDuration/> turns\n<Bullet/> Shield strength increases as the architect's spire kit is upgraded."

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_SpireShelter X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Shelter"
LocLongDescription="Contact with a spire has granted this soldier a shield."
LocHelpText="Contact with a spire has granted this soldier a shield."
LocFlyOverText="Shelter"
LocPromotionPopupText="The shield lasts for <Ability:ShelterShieldDuration/> turns."

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_Quicksilver X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Quicksilver Rigging"
LocLongDescription="Your spires gain Quicksilver, an ability which grants an adjacent squadmate an action point. "
LocHelpText="Your spires gain Quicksilver, an ability which grants an adjacent squadmate an extra action once per mission."
LocFlyOverText="Quicksilver Rigging"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"A personal favorite of Prompto Argentum.\"\n\nQuicksilver contributes powerful utility to your team, enabling deep strikes from rangers and templars or rapid repositioning from a sharpshooter.\n\n<Bullet/> Spire must be activated to use Quicksilver\n<Bullet/> Each use of Quicksilver costs one of the spire's Quicksilver charges\n<Bullet/> The action point is granted instantly, and it can be given to any adjacent squadmate - even if they've used all of their action points for the turn"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_SpireQuicksilver X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Quicksilver"
LocLongDescription="Grant a bonus action immediately to an adjacent squadmate."
LocHelpText="Grant a bonus action immediately to an adjacent squadmate."
LocFlyOverText="Quicksilver"
LocPromotionPopupText="LIGHTNING!"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_FieldReloadModule X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Field Reload Array"
LocLongDescription="When you create a spire, it restores some ammo to allies adjacent to it."
LocHelpText="When you create a spire, it restores some ammo to allies adjacent to it."
LocFlyOverText="Field Reload Array"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"No one cares whether it's called a mag or a clip when there's 600 pounds of Muton bearing down on them.\"\n\nField Reload Array guarantees utility of your spires on the turn they're placed. It's especially powerful for a squadmates holding weapons with small clips.\n\n<Bullet/> Passive\n<Bullet/> Works for any spire you create, including ones created with Headstone."

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_SpireFieldReloadModule X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Field Reload Array"
LocLongDescription="This spire restored ammo to adjacent allies when it spawned."
LocFlyOverText="Field Reload Array"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_TransmatLink X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="The Swapper"
LocLongDescription="Exchange locations with one of your spires."
LocHelpText="Exchange locations with one of your spires."
LocFlyOverText="The Swapper"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"You tell everyone it's just a lucky rabbit's foot. No one has yet pointed out that most rabbits' feet don't glow bright orange.\"\n\nThe Swapper allows the Architect to reposition quickly, enabling safe retreat and aggressive engagement. It's also useful for bringing cover to an ally in need if Build Spire is on cooldown.\n\n<Bullet/> Free action\n<Bullet/> <Ability:TransmatLinkCooldown/>-turn cooldown"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_Reclaim X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Reclaim"
LocLongDescription="Destroy an adjacent spire. You gain one action point, and the cooldown of Build Spire resets."
LocHelpText="Destroy an adjacent spire. You gain one action point, and the cooldown of Build Spire resets."
LocFlyOverText="Reclaim"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Reduce. Reuse. Recycle.\"\n\n<Bullet/> Free action\n<Bullet/> <Ability:ReclaimCooldown/>-turn cooldown"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_Headstone X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Headstone"
LocLongDescription="Summon a spire on a tile occupied by the corpse of an enemy."
LocHelpText="Summon a spire on a tile occupied by the corpse of an enemy."
LocFlyOverText="Headstone"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Rest in peace.\"\n\nHeadstone doesn't share a cooldown with Build Spire, so it increases the rate at which you can create spires considerably.\n\n<Bullet/> Free action\n<Bullet/> <Ability:HeadstoneCooldown/>-turn cooldown\n<Bullet/> Can target any enemy corpse in visual range of the Architect"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_TargetingArray X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Targeting Array"
LocLongDescription="Your spires gain Targeting Array, a passive ability that enhances the accuracy of adjacent squadmates."
LocHelpText="Your spires gain Targeting Array, a passive ability that enhances the accuracy of adjacent squadmates."
LocFlyOverText="Targeting Array"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Not bad for a start. The next version will fit on their guns.\"\n- Chief Engineer Shen\n\n<Bullet/> Passive"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_SpireTargetingArray X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Targeting Array"
