LocFriendlyName="Targeting Array Online"
LocLongDescription="The nearby spire's targeting array is online, enhancing the accuracy of your shots."
LocHelpText="The nearby spire's targeting array is online, enhancing the accuracy of your shots."
LocFlyOverText="Targeting Array"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Not bad for a start. The next version will fit on their guns.\"\n- Chief Engineer Shen\n\n<Bullet/> Passive"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_KineticRigging X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Kinetic Rigging"
LocLongDescription="Your spires gain Kinetic Blast, an ability that knocks back all enemies in the area of effect."
LocHelpText="Your spires gain Kinetic Blast, an ability that knocks back all enemies in the area of effect."
LocFlyOverText="Kinetic Rigging"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Advent may have dispensed with the use of nonlethal force, but we haven't. Well... not while they're in cover, anyway.\"\n\n<Bullet/> Spire must be activated to use Kinetic Blast"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_KineticBlast X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Kinetic Blast"
LocLongDescription="The spire emits a blast of pure kinetic energy, knocking back all targets in the area of effect."
LocHelpText="The spire emits a blast of pure kinetic energy, knocking back all targets in the area of effect."
LocFlyOverText="Kinetic Blast"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Advent may have dispensed with the use of nonlethal force, but we haven't. Well... not while they're in cover, anyway.\""

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_Unity X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Unity"
LocLongDescription="You can use Build Spire on tiles adjacent to allies."
LocHelpText="You can use Build Spire on tiles adjacent to allies."
LocFlyOverText="Unity"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"You sense this will have a MASSive EFFECT on your tactical engagements.\"\n\nYou can still place spires around you in the same range as you could without Unity - it just adds the tiles adjacent to your visible squadmates as additional options.\n\n<Bullet/> Passive"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_RelayedShot X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Relayed Shot"
LocLongDescription="Fire your <Ability:WeaponName/> at one of your spires. The spire increases its range and causes it to overpenetrate all targets in the area of effect. Costs extra ammo."
LocHelpText="Fire your <Ability:WeaponName/> at one of your spires. The spire increases its range and causes it to overpenetrate all targets in the area of effect. Costs extra ammo."
LocFlyOverText="Relayed Shot"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"These new recruits don't even have to aim. I'm gettin' too old for this.\"\nCentral Officer Bradford\n\nRelayed Shot deals the damage of your primary weapon to all targets in the area of effect. This makes architects with this ability especially good ammo carriers, since special ammunition effects are also applied.\n\n<Bullet/> <Ability:RelayedShotCooldown/>-turn cooldown\n<Bullet/> Empties your clip\n<Bullet/> Ends your turn"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_SoulOfTheArchitect X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Soul of the Architect"
LocLongDescription="All effects that apply to your spires also apply to you. You gain all abilities that your spires have."
LocHelpText="All effects that apply to your spires also apply to you. You gain all abilities that your spires have."
LocFlyOverText="Soul of the Architect"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"We shape our buildings; thereafter they shape us.\"\n- Winston Churchill\n\nSoul of the Architect makes you, in many ways, functionally similar to your spires. You provide high cover to your squad, and any other perks you've gained that affect your spires also apply to you passively.\n\n<Bullet/> Some skills that don't have cooldowns on your spires do when you gain them via Soul of the Architect\n<Bullet/> Kinetic Blast has a <Ability:KineticBlastCooldownWithSoul/>-turn cooldown\n<Bullet/> Quicksilver has a <Ability:QuicksilverCooldownWithSoul/>-turn cooldown\n<Bullet/> You don't apply Targeting Array or Shelter Array to yourself"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_TransmatNetwork X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Transmat Network"
LocLongDescription="Your spires gain Transmat Network Node. When a squadmate is adjacent to a node, they can use Transmat, a free ability that allows them to relocate to any space adjacent to a spire in the network. 1-turn global cooldown."
LocHelpText="Your spires gain Transmat Network Node. When a squadmate is adjacent to a node, they can use Transmat, a free ability that allows them to relocate to any space adjacent to a spire in the network. 1-turn global cooldown."
LocFlyOverText="Transmat Network"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Everything has to be somewhere. The trick is having the right things be in the right places.\"\n\n<Bullet/> Transmat is usable once per turn, but any member of your squad adjacent to a spire can use it\n<Bullet/> The Transmat ability doesn't cost an action\n<Bullet/> Civilians like VIPs can't use the Transmat ability, but non-XCOM units like hacked or mind-controlled enemies can"

[Jammerware_JSRC_Ability_SpireTransmatNetwork X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Transmat Network Node"
LocLongDescription="Once per turn, a squadmate can activate Transmat when adjacent to this spire, relocating to another space adjacent any spire in the network."
LocHelpText="Squadmates can active Transmat when adjacent to this spire, relocating to another space adjacent any spire in the network."
LocFlyOverText="Transmat Network Node"
LocPromotionPopupText="\"Everything has to be somewhere. The trick is having the right things be in the right places.\""

